# Nostr Forum - Environment Configuration

Copy this file to `.env` and fill in your values:

```bash
cp .env.example .env
```

## Required Variables

```env
# Nostr Relays (comma-separated)
VITE_NOSTR_RELAYS=ws://localhost:4433,wss://relay.damus.io,wss://relay.nostr.band

# Development Mode (set to 'true' for dev key auto-login)
VITE_DEV_MODE=false

# Development Private Key (NEVER use in production!)
# Generate with: nostr-tool generate-key
# VITE_DEV_NSEC=nsec1...
```

## Security Warning

⚠️ **NEVER commit your `.env` file or private keys to git!**

The `.env` file is already in `.gitignore` but always double-check before committing.

## Development Mode

When `VITE_DEV_MODE=true`, the app will automatically log in with the development key.
This is useful for testing but should NEVER be enabled in production.

## Production Deployment

For production:
1. Set `VITE_DEV_MODE=false`
2. Remove or comment out `VITE_DEV_NSEC`
3. Users will use NIP-07 browser extensions (like Alby) to log in
